description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a Medical Secretary to join our busy secretarial team within the Histopathology Department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a full time post working predominantly at the QMC Campus although you will also be expected to work at the City campus as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be working as part of a team and required to use your own initiative to provide a complete medical secretarial service for the Consultant Histopathologists. These teams are also a key point of reference for hospital staff and outside agencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You need a minimum 2 year&#39;s previous secretarial/administrative experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must possess 4 GCSEs or equivalent including English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be an enthusiastic and conscientious team player with excellent communication skills, able to use your own initiative and be able to respond to queries in a diplomatic and professional manner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to demonstrate a clear understanding of confidentiality issues, be well motivated and reliable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameVictoria BennettJob titleAdmin ManagerEmail addressvictoria.bennett@nuh.nhs.ukTelephone number01159249924 Ext 83661Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
